solution: ```class Solution {
    public int smallestRepunitDivByK(int k) {
        if (k % 2 == 0 || k % 5 == 0) return -1;
        int rem = 0;
        for (int len = 1; len <= k; len++) {
            rem = (rem * 10 + 1) % k;
            if (rem == 0) return len;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(k)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses modular arithmetic to avoid huge numbers; checks divisibility by 2 or 5 early; loops at most k times due to pigeonhole principle.

